            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>IaC Telecom Automation is a backend infrastructure project demonstrating a modern deployment workflow using containerization and cloud-native architecture. The project models how backend services are packaged, stored, and deployed through automated infrastructure processes rather than manual server configuration.</p>
            
            <p>The system simulates a telecom backend deployed on AWS, where Docker images are built once, stored in AWS Elastic Container Registry (ECR), and executed on cloud instances to ensure consistent and reproducible environments.</p>

            <h2>Key Highlights</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Backend service containerized using Docker</li>
                <li>Image-based deployment through AWS ECR</li>
                <li>Cloud execution on AWS EC2</li>
                <li>Environment-driven configuration and stateless service design</li>
                <li>Foundation prepared for Terraform-based infrastructure provisioning and Kubernetes orchestration</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Purpose</h2>
            <p>The project demonstrates how Infrastructure as Code principles enable repeatable, scalable, and reliable backend deployments aligned with real-world production systems.</p>
